quran[18]{c,v,t,f}:
  51,40,"So We took him and his soldiers and cast them into the sea, and he was blameworthy."
  51,41,"And in ʿAad [was a sign], when We sent against them the barren wind.{1}",footnotes:1:[Barren of any benefit, i.e., evil.]
  51,42,"It left nothing of what it came upon but that it made it like disintegrated ruins."
  52,31,"Say, "
  52,32,"Or do their minds{1} command them to [say] this, or are they a transgressing people?",footnotes:1:[In this expression is also a subtle allusion to the leaders of the Quraysh, who considered themselves to be great minds.]
  52,33,"Or do they say, "
  53,25,"Rather, to Allāh belongs the Hereafter and the first [life]."
  53,26,"And how many angels there are in the heavens whose intercession will not avail at all except [only] after Allāh has permitted [it] to whom He wills and approves."
  53,27,"Indeed, those who do not believe in the Hereafter name the angels female names,"
  54,16,"And how [severe] were My punishment and warning.{1}",footnotes:1:[To those after them, who were expected to derive a lesson from previous occurrences.]
  54,17,"And We have certainly made the Qur’ān easy for remembrance, so is there any who will remember?"
  54,18,"ʿAad denied; and how [severe] were My punishment and warning."
  55,10,"And the earth He laid [out] for the creatures."
  55,11,"Therein is fruit and palm trees having sheaths [of dates]"
  55,12,"And grain having husks and scented plants."
  56,1,"When the Occurrence occurs,"
  56,2,"There is, at its occurrence, no denial."
  56,3,"It will bring down [some] and raise up [others].{1}",footnotes:1:[According to their deeds rather than wealth and social position, as is the case in this world.]
